result.execSummary:
The defendant Zohn Wang Kub Yang was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Zohn Wang Kub Yang is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Zohn Wang Kub Yang was found guilty of Attempt 1st-Degree Intentional Homicide [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.01(1)(a).
  • Zohn Wang Kub Yang was found guilty of Aggravated Battery-Intend GreatBod. Harm [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(5).
  • Zohn Wang Kub Yang was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Zohn Wang Kub Yang was found guilty of Criminal Damage to Property [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).
  • Zohn Wang Kub Yang was found guilty of Criminal Damage to Property [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).
  • Zohn Wang Kub Yang was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Zohn Wang Kub Yang was found guilty of Endanger Safety/Use/Dangerous Weapon [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 941.20(1)(a).
  • Zohn Wang Kub Yang was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.
